ŐUŻ‚H!`ţ%]j24ŁKZ}ÖJÉT7LL{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "a6b3eb70-f84c-445b-9b01-7e70b340f968", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "81cb65d2e98e9c2ab1cfb969f7006d06437e1ddb77a3f260dc035b923b6165c7"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "BA_Harrison", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-05", "title": null, "content": "There's not a whole lot of originality about the basic premise for Cold Storage: how many times have we seen films about deadly micro-organisms threatening humanity? That said, I still had a good time with this goofy horror comedy, thanks to likeable performances from its leads (Barbarian's Georgina Campbell, Stranger Things' Joe Keery, and Liam Neeson) and a whole load of gloopy silliness, as a parasitic fungus transforms people (and animals) into zombies that have a nasty habit of erupting in a mess of slime and body parts.\n\nKeery and Campbell play Teacake and Naomi, security guards at a self-storage company located on the site of an old military base. When a highly contagious fungus - stored deep in the bowels of the facility - escapes containment, an aging bio-terror operative, played by Neeson, must try to neutralise the threat before it gets out of control. Keery and Campbell share good chemistry, but Neeson is the standout here, getting all the best lines as the grizzled tough guy who isn't averse to detonating a nuke to get the job done, much to the consternation of the youngsters caught in the midst of the outbreak.\n\nThe film isn't perfect: there's some dodgy CGI in use - a few of the special effects wouldn't look out of place in a film from twenty years ago - David Koepp's script delivers little in the way of genuine surprises, and the direction by Jonny Campbell is merely workmanlike, as one might expect from someone whose career has been primarily in TV. But the film was never intended to be high art... it's a 'not-to-be-taken-seriously, Friday night, kick back, have a few beers and enjoy' kind of film - simple escapism that doesn't tax the brain, carefully crafted to provide a few giggles and plenty of gross out moments. And that's exactly what it does."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "2c73fc39-6761-40cc-9461-009aaa3ff200", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "42265a8a3a5cf7461851eb09b0440277820604cc0bb89fdbfc265e3331866cad"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "jared-25331", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-14", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage (2026) is a horror comedy movie written by David Koepp based on his 2019 novel of the same name and it follows a group of characters attempting to contain a parasitic fungus that leaks out of an abandoned military base. This is a movie that I was excited to watch because of the cast and David Koepp, so I waited for the chance to watch it and the movie was awesome.\n\nPositives for Cold Storage (2026): The story is a unique take on the zombie subgenre with a couple of changes being made in the main narrative that were interesting. The movie goes for a B-movie feel that works for the premise. You have a fun ensemble cast with Georgina Campbell, Joe Keery, Sosie Bacon, Vanessa Redgrave, Lesley Manville and Liam Neeson, who know exactly what movie they're in. I like how everyone is serious but not too serious to the point where the story falls apart and are committed to their performances. The zombie style horror is handled very well with the use of practical and digital effects that are a mix of being terrifying and goofy. The movie has a good pace as the story flows perfectly with time flying by so fast that I didn't moticed it for a while. And finally, this is a nice hangout horror comedy movies that you can enjoy with some family and friends for a couple of hours at the theater.\n\nNegatives for Cold Storage (2026): The movie feels a little uneven with the pacing as it doesn't give you time to breathe as it wants to get to the ending faster.\n\nOverall, Cold Storage (2026) is a good silly horror comedy movie that is fun for fans of the genre and I would definitely recommend it if you're looking for some dumb fun that can be serious at times."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "2e526d68-bedc-4a58-9f65-33be0552ebf3", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "983cba0fb1e6b0254ec369988b90d3f6020d508655a4b5c5fbc436f5788c6d53"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "jwcstorage", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-16", "title": null, "content": "I wanna give this a 6.5.\n\nI didnt know this movie existed and so I went in probably the most blind of any movie I've ever seen.\n\nAt first, I was wondering why Liam Neeson was acting like he was in a B movie, especially as the opening is played fairly dark. After realizing what the movie actually was, I understood and I got into the movie more.\n\nIts a freaky, kinda goofy black comedy that shows its true colors (green, and lots of it!) the longer it goes on.\n\nIts a pretty fun body horror that if you can gel with the dark tone mixed with the comedy aspects its a fine popcorn flick worthy of a watch. It didnt get any out loud laughs, but air was definitely expelled with moderate force through my nose at several times.\n\nThis is one of those rare mid-good movies where I'm not sure how it could've been improved as all the pieces generally fit. If they went more serious, it'd feel derivative but if they went sillier it'd be too goofy for the material."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e262b004-007f-46ef-b931-572a852a0f13", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a1857de082dff42688b0530102f034d60e5b677620d387a6cae4b0892faa39ec"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Chris4Reel4Real", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-12", "title": null, "content": "When a deadly fungus escapes from a secret laboratory, a former bioterrorism agent teams up with two young employees to stop an invisible threat before it spreads beyond control.\n\nCold Storage is gross, fun, and genuinely entertaining. It has a strong central premise and some sharp writing, but I kept wishing it would lean harder into the absurdity of its situation. There are flashes of camp and chaos that feel like they're about to explode into something cult-worthy... and then the film reins itself back in.\n\nJoe Keery does an impressive job separating this performance from his most recognizable role. His speech patterns and physicality feel distinct, and it works. Georgina Campbell brings real charisma, and Liam Neeson once again proves he's excellent at playing a completely serious character in a slightly ridiculous scenario.\n\nThe special effects are mostly strong. The infected wildlife and fungal growths look convincing, minus one rough deer shot. Visually it works more often than not.\n\nTonally, it sits somewhere in the neighborhood of Return of the Living Dead, but never quite commits to that level of camp or chaos. If it had pushed further in that direction, it might have elevated from entertaining to unforgettable.\n\nAs it stands, it's a solid \"Middle of the Morgue\" entry. Some good, some bad, but absolutely a good time."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "4c01dac0-4de7-4251-be46-bc740cb8225a", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "18e1d86c68125536d08fa7b3ee8207a0408dd69387194e4aa4bd9354e1dec48d"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "ColinTheGorilla", "rating": 4, "date": "2026-02-17", "title": null, "content": "So I didn't really know what I was going to get into with this film and I had no idea going in and I found it to be meh. At some points of the movie it's pretty decent for the most part but some parts felt so off to me. The movie has a pretty solid cast with Joe Kerry, Georgina Campbell and Liam Neeson and I found most of the performances to be alright and pretty goofy for the most part and I think one of the best parts of the film was the chemistry between Joe Kerry and Georgina Campbell's characters and I found their dynamic to be interesting. Liam Neeson does a decent job but he feels kinda out of place doing his serious acting and comedic acting in this film. The story is decent and pretty easy to follow which made the movie easier to watch because of the straight basic storyline which the movie doesn't do a whole lot of interesting things with its premise but I see the idea they had. Whenever the film tries to introduce som humor as well it's very hit or miss there's a few jokes in here which made me laugh a little bit but I felt like there were more misses than hits with the jokes for the most part. I also think the fungus is designed really nice throughout the movie however I didn't like how some of the people or animals ended up looking like near the later half of the movie and it felt like they were rushing to finish the designs and the CGI is also a little weird at times as well because it looks really goofy throughout the movie and it helps the movie sometimes with some of the comedy but sometimes it just brings the movie down as well. The movie also feels like the pace is bringing it down as well because some part of the movie felt very slow compared to some parts of the movie which just goes by action quickly and doesn't expand on some things introduced as well. I feel like this is a movie which is perfect for streaming and it's eh but it doesn't do a whole lot of interesting things unfortunately."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "d1b751b8-095a-48da-8aeb-4dfef7ae0013", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "1811637cea8aab4d657b21b8155fa975b16d5944d7f98078862ccdca7a282318"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "TheMovieSearch", "rating": 4, "date": "2026-02-16", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage is a 2026 sci-fi comedy that leans heavily into campy humor, with Joe Keery delivering an over-the-top performance that borders on goofy, and Georgina Campbell matching that tone with her own quirky antics. Liam Neeson, once a reliable action star, feels typecast in this film, giving an almost copy-and-paste performance that fits the comedic tone but lacks originality. The premise-a space-borne fungus landing on Earth and threatening global chaos-could have been tense or thrilling, but instead the movie chooses spoof and absurdity over seriousness, leaning into ridiculous situations rather than genuine suspense.\n\nThe screenplay delivers jokes and gags but often lands unevenly, with corny dialogue that occasionally interrupts the flow. The pacing is adequate, though the film never really reaches a cinematic peak, reinforcing the sense that it is designed primarily for streaming rather than theatrical release. Certain sequences are visually entertaining, and the director makes competent use of the cast and limited effects to keep scenes moving, though nothing feels particularly innovative or memorable.\n\nDespite its flaws, Cold Storage has a light, watchable quality for audiences willing to accept a goofy, over-the-top premise. It succeeds as a streaming comedy rather than a blockbuster cinematic event, providing laughs more than thrills. The chemistry among the leads works well in moments, but the narrative is far too thin and reliant on silliness to sustain real tension.\n\nUltimately, this film is a fun, harmless diversion that doesn't aim to break new ground. Fans of Joe Keery's quirkiness or Neeson's occasional comedic turns may find enjoyment, but serious sci-fi or action viewers might be disappointed. It's better suited for casual streaming viewing rather than a theater experience. The movie is amusing in bursts, but the reliance on spoof humor keeps it from being anything more substantial, making it a light, forgettable entry in 2026's film lineup."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "ea69c489-330e-4dcb-960d-b77e53e005ec", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "be67affb87283758dbac961803cddd360e00262c6af75f4416469880bdff2b77"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "slightlymad22", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-26", "title": null, "content": "I just got out of Cold Storage\n\nThis is a tough one to find great things to say about, Joe Keery (Steve in Stranger Things) was fine, as was Georgina Campbell and Liam Neeson goes through the motions of performing in a part than has no lines worth speaking!!\n\nIt all just felt like a waste of time, I was pretty bored for most of it, as it's only vaguely engaging and pretty much instantly forgettable.\n\nTrailers shown were\n\nHow To Make A Killing Mortal Kombat 2 Ready Or Not 2 The Bride (I'm sick of seeing this trailer) Scream 7 Project Hail Mary\n\nThere were other three people in my screening."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "15c8302f-f79e-4ab9-a8c3-ee29e0aa5a37", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "dab007af4c2e828240eeda1e46ddef7071da2e21e2acba41e99b4a32c6c1c24a"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "nERDbOX_Dave", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-13", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage might be the horror-comedy jolt I didn't know I needed. After feeling like I was crawling out of the cinematic void of Gale: Yellow Brick Road, this one plays like a spiritual rebound, loud, gross, chaotic, and refreshingly self-aware. If last year's Ick walked so weird science horror-comedy could run, Cold Storage sprints straight into exploding fungal madness.\n\nDirected by Jonny Campbell and adapted by David Koepp from his own novel, the film centers on what should be a boring overnight shift at a self-storage facility. Instead, it turns into ground zero for a government screw-up decades in the making. What starts as an investigation into an annoying dying battery beep... yes, that smoke alarm chirp that makes you question your sanity,spirals into the discovery of a long-forgotten containment unit buried beneath the facility. Only it's not a smoke alarm that's dying. It's a biological failsafe... and it's about to shut down.\n\nThis rapidly mutating fungus sealed away in 1978 by government agents Robert Quinn (Liam Neeson) and Trini Romano (Lesley Manville), begins creeping through the facility as temperatures rise. What follows is a brain-controlling, body-bursting nightmare that turns storage renters and unlucky employees into twitchy, boom-prone zombie drones. It's gross. It's ridiculous. And it's wildly entertaining.\n\nGeorgina Campbell brings grounded intensity as Naomi Williams, anchoring the film emotionally while chaos unfolds around her. Joe Keery, as Travis \"Teacake\" Meacham, once again proves he has that lovable chaos energy dialed in perfectly. His performance balances awkward humor with real panic in a way that feels effortless.\n\nNeeson leans into the absurdity here with his comedic timing. His straight-faced delivery in the middle of escalating fungal insanity is some of the film's best humor. Paired with Lesley Manville's dry wit, the two veteran actors add a strange credibility to the madness. They're the last remaining witnesses to the parasite's original outbreak, and when the containment system begins its shutdown cycle, it's up to them and a couple of self-storage employees who definitely did not sign up for this to stop history from repeating itself.\n\nCold Storage strikes a solid balance between practical effects and CGI. The body horror sequences, bursting spores, twitching limbs, fungal tendrils creeping through air vents are tactile enough to feel real without over-relying on digital gloss. If I have one complaint, it's that I wanted more of the creeping dread: more time watching the fungus spread, infect random objects, mutate in unpredictable ways. The setup is so fun that you almost wish the film let it simmer just a little longer before going full explosion mode.\n\nTonally, the film lands comfortably between The Thing and Shaun of the Dead, with a sprinkle of Return of the Living Dead chaos. It understands that horror-comedy works best when the horror is played seriously and the comedy comes from character reactions not winks at the camera. And for the most part, it nails that balance.\n\nIn the end, Cold Storage is exactly what it promises: a fast, funny, occasionally gnarly creature feature with enough heart and humor to make the mayhem worth it. It's a reminder that sometimes the best horror-comedies come from simple premises, like a dying battery beep in the middle of the night and asking, \"What if that noise meant the world was about to end?\""}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "5d7a2a53-5f9f-4cab-af6e-d5f6a8087789", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "692e3b6459512d07ca5ae9c9924811ea9eeb17a8b1d3b4a987e88b4f09009bff"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "keikoyoshikawa", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "I must admit: I got tired of seeing Liam Neeson in old-guy action movies. So it was a pleasant and welcomed surprise to see him in this sci-fi, horror, comedy film.\n\nTight story, good action, good acting. Characters didn't do (mostly) dumb stuff. Believable actions and reactions are what makes for immersion. Overall, it was a short, fun movie to watch.\n\nShout out to Joe Keery and Georgina Campbell - as Travis and Naomi - for their performances, which really helped to sell the story."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "16eacdfa-a4f8-458b-9c61-2458f60f918a", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "dce5c82ec50f62904bb51dc4c51f8f904e8fcc6560c238c97764efa1a4221bf2"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "BennyTheHellraiserFan", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-07", "title": null, "content": "This movie is just very fun. There is no big complicated plot that requires you to use your brain. Just turn your brain off and enjoy things getting blown up.\n\nThe movie is very unoriginal but still very entertaining. It's essentially just a modern Troma movie. Just as much guts, gore, explosions and gross-out moments as our favorite Troma movies. Unlike Troma the comedy in this movie doesn't consist of offensive stereotypes. A lot of the comedy landed for me and I did still think it was very funny. Liam Neeson is great in the movie and the reason for some of the funniest moments in the film.\n\nOne of the movies greatest strengths are the good characters, the great acting, the decent cgi and the none stop action.\n\nIf you like explosions both of the gooey, splattery kind and of the nuclear kind you will be satisfied. The movie is not the best thing ever but it's still super fun and entertaining."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "decbca62-8724-4be4-b5c4-7a18e2998ba9", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ae508b8877ee0937fa277d18606b4df32e1f7117083f7e6df7faab324fb82b3c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "meinredmi", "rating": 4, "date": "2026-03-08", "title": null, "content": "After my trip to the cinema, I unfortunately have to say that I walked out of the theater quite disappointed. My anticipation after seeing the trailer had actually been very high, since it had already created a bit of hype for me.\n\nThe opening is actually quite well done. The first few minutes are excitingly staged and raise hopes for an entertaining and energetic \"horror\" film. At the beginning, I therefore had certain expectations about how the story would develop.\n\nUnfortunately, as the film goes on, it never really manages to pick up momentum for me. Even though the runtime is relatively short at just a little over 90 minutes, the film still feels somewhat sluggish at times and only really starts to gain a bit of momentum rather late. There are a little handful of splatter effects and some interesting camera movements. Stylistically, it sometimes feels like a homage to the fun B-horror movies of earlier times. Nevertheless, much of it remains too tame and doesn't feel as consistently executed as one might have hoped.\n\nMaybe it was also due to the budget, which might have been too limited. Some ideas seem like they had more potential, but in the end that potential was never fully realized. What I found particularly disappointing was the lack of a truly gripping showdown-this is exactly where the film could have really gone all out. But no such luck.\n\nThat said, not everything is bad: the main actors come across as likable, the film actually looks quite good visually for a B-movie, and the soundtrack offers a few nice musical moments here and there.\n\nAll in all, however, it remains a major disappointment for me. Despite some good ideas and likable actors, the film couldn't live up to my expectations-and unfortunately, the trip to the cinema wasn't really worth the money in the end.\n\n4.4/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "d51b0eea-f36f-478b-ab12-9414bd6d8e9b", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c58abdae866a3a261a927fe7474f7e9d4e52e3c54421a31b86e841d6a1786467"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "HardyReviews_", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-16", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage is a relaxing comedy with some memorable moments. This film does have some rough visual effects, but the practical effects are actually impressive. Everyone involved made this movie a great watch and this movie is a film that you can watch with family and friends, and all will have a great time."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "deb2d20f-550e-4b6a-8da1-95b811285c99", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "49b74ae120a1d9f22f980391a3b19772089f328d87164aa468669c8d7e6a9975"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "PWray_99", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-14", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage is a horror comedy about two self- storage workers who have to prevent an infectious fungus from spreading and taking over the world. The fungus is nothing new from any kind of virus in movies and at times is very reminiscent of Last of Us. I love the design of the infected at the beginning of the movie unfortunately the designs get a little lazier as the movie progresses. The cast is fine. I like Joe Keery as an actor so it was good to see him. Georgina Campbell was good too. Liam Neeson was ok, he was a mixture of his \"Taken\" serious side and \"Naked Gun\" comedy side. The story was fine. This is a good horror movie to watch at home with friends."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "a68d97b6-1ae2-4186-b6d6-7d8ba7eecc42", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e57a94931ed2a7c56dd77ed52eff2d49fa6ff9d4ecbddb7fbf9cd2c34f7d4f20"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "vengeance20", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-21", "title": null, "content": "So, I saw this advertised & thought it might be good. I wasn't expecting much, but given I'm a Liam Neeson fan, I thought I'd see it.\n\nWhen a highly dangerous Fungus escapes from a secret laboratory, a former Bioterrorism Agent is called back into action. Alongside 2 young employees, he must confront an invisible & out-of-control threat.\n\nI found the film to be pretty good. It's not amazing as such but it pretty much does the job for what it is. The plot isn't great & a bit thin I will say, but, it's simple & doesn't require you to think to much. The actors including Liam do a good job here with their roles & there's plenty of action, some gore & a bit of eye candy with the women.\n\nThe films runtime is 1 hour & 32 minutes long (92 minutes) & has pretty decent pacing too. The films ending was good & the effects here were pretty good too despite looking a bit fake in places. Despite some modern social commentary being added in which I felt was unneeded, I liked this one. In terms of the Horror it was good, the comedy could've used some work though.\n\nOverall, it's a decent Horror Comedy flick. It's nothing special as such, but it's good enough & one you can enjoy with your mates. I'd recommend this one.\n\n7/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "8a0862b1-9054-4701-a030-3729a8832051", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e6d3e76af6da57e8004c5b7b303408bb1bfd0d4f45f773e948360d5ae239d77e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Luv2Spooge", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "When you have an American comedy and you start off with people just talking talking talking a lot for no reason, you know this is utter crap. And... it is.\n\nLet me put it this way, it takes 50 mins to get to the discovery of the fungus exposure. 50 mins in a movie that is 1 hr and 30 mins. And it is not a spoiler since the intro scene already revealed the horror element is the fungus.\n\nSo literally rest of this movie is utterly pointless cheap CGI.\n\n1/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "d9b57692-96cb-415e-90db-e8061cf0f046", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.799523", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c84190c27b7a183837f1a897e1174e396372e9137567797bd8f951c713407f53"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "erw-67672", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-18", "title": null, "content": "I read the novel a few years ago and was surprised to find that the film follows the book more closely than many many other book-to-film conversions.\n\nIf you blend Crichton's The Andromeda Strain with King's Dreamcatcher.... you get Vold Storage. A fun, end-of-the-world type situation.\n\nGlad to see Joe Kerry getting more work, and Lesley Manville who seems to have an outstanding agent, because she is getting SO MANY roles in film and TV!!!\n\nExcuse me now.... I feel a need to climb up onto my roof."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "5df959c4-49bf-48f5-b2d8-d428e96c2a68", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800524", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "66bc5e0a5796e8024b3f25d80b180ce8f56f2c5b3b809db236a4ca54a9188c39"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "MrR-4905", "rating": 2, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "The trailers looked like it might be a fun horror comedy.\n\nBut it wasn't.\n\nI didn't have high hopes, and it failed to live up to them.\n\nIf you've seen the trailer, you've seen all the jokes. Worse, the best joke in the trailer is an edit and doesn't occur in the film.\n\nIt seemed to start well, and Neeson's sarcasm level was spot on. Cut to the present, settle in with a hot drink and nod off, it's quite dull from here on in.\n\nThe scene where the bomb goes off, near the end is truly dreadful, and the whole film had enough plot holes to be a string vest."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e282e561-a49d-48f5-9afc-e06c2483502e", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800524", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "987d58ddc2f38d64570fcdf07b5c6838cf63c9fb065e44e1834478959d227e94"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "paul_m_haakonsen", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-06", "title": null, "content": "Well, I had actually not even heard about this 2026 movie prior to stumbling upon it by sheer chance. And since it as a movie with Liam Neeson on the cast list, and it being a movie that I hadn't already seen, of course I opted to give the movie a fair chance.\n\nWriter David Koepp penned down a rather enjoyable script and storyline. It was pretty straightforward, but it was also unique at the same time. I do like the fungal infection aspect of the movie, because it was certainly a nice touch to the movie.\n\nOf the entire cast ensemble in the movie, I actually do believe that I was only familiar with Liam Neeson, Joe Keery and Richard Brake. The acting performances in \"Cold Storage\" were good.\n\nThe effects in \"Cold Storage\" were good, and that certainly added a lot of enjoyment to the overall movie. So thumbs up for that. And it is rather crucial for a movie such as this to have proper effects to make the audience buy into it.\n\nMy rating of director Jonny Campbell's movie \"Cold Storage\" lands on a six out of ten stars."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "50089e92-4ecb-45be-a7d5-0b5ea90f6970", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800524", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a95b08efe026e9124f5dae65d3622b062c6ad37e926b785e2bb05f3037e2dab9"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "FeastMode", "rating": 4, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "Even though this movie was released in theaters, it feels very streamy. Most aspects are lower in quality than you would expect from a theatrical movie. There is some questionable stuff, poor CGI, and a general lack of investment. And most of the comedy doesn't land for me.\n\nThe best parts are the chemistry between Teacake and Naomi, as well as something early that reminded me of the first Scream movie. But I found this to be mostly underwhelming.\n\n(1 viewing, 3/6/2026)"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "f8425c4d-222f-49bc-9a3b-db88132ff7fb", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800524", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a0d164cac67de3e13dfaaafa3d1ba6d2a920fc976cfa2c79c634c59e3c22e147"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "LordCommandar", "rating": 2, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "The reviews got this wrong. Bad story along with bad acting except from Liam Neesom. I guess Hollywood dumps all the trash films between Jan-Feb as the year comes in and Cold Storage fits right into the category of ridiculous production. Don't believe any of the positive reviews. This film was just dumb."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "55442ea4-7c2d-41e1-a117-73446867eb3f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800524", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "beabf6f76a741f9b5869014055f66a20f47057934efb64525792eac77f3a97f3"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "PsychoBeard666", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-26", "title": null, "content": "My criticisms: the CGI isn't up to much and some of the jokes from side characters didn't land because of the delivery. The trailer implies a tone closer to Zombieland but it never hits those levels of humour.\n\nThe good bits: everything else. Stellar acting, an entertaining plot that moves at a decent pace, good gore, likeable lead characters and deservedly unlikeable antagonists.\n\nDefinitely worth a watch."}}
