{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "f16b76f5-ab78-486d-845d-fea0d2e687e3", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800524", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "3de35f4003e59d02b1b421b194a65c997349294e7acac7225020976933e95442"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "TheW-019", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-02-20", "title": null, "content": "Couldn't care less for the characters. Those many plot holes were not funn either. Yes, it's a B-movie, but not funny enough for a B-movie. The humor didn't catch me. I managed a few laughs only.\n\nI hardly remeber the plot. It was just... Who cares?\n\nThe characters don't make any sense. From teenage pregnancy over conviction to scientific genious. Makes no sense to you, what I'm saying? Because this is how this movie goes.\n\nThe acting was also really bad."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "4035582b-547c-4e93-a618-c209bbf18f8e", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800524", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "7da01f0a957742da2afda1a316a6efd92bfa0ba634e94aa0b5b96b7121b9e0fc"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "MichaelD-7925", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-13", "title": null, "content": "Joe keery and everyone else did an amazing job in this! Was even better than I expected! My favorite movie of the year so far! Great story, some jumps, lots of humor and lots of gores. Warning for anyone who's an animal lover: watch w caution! I will def be seeing this ago and again! Especially extra Recommend if ur a fan of Joe keery!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "6006ab58-1eb0-453d-89bd-0a4a40e05520", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800971", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "cf6d8de33e3c1223cd048e9fdc6ccd742c40ec65f3e94f159110353a4aadc047"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "AlliS-10", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-16", "title": null, "content": "Absolutely amazing movie. In my opinion, it was very well executed for its genre, and I could see it becoming a cult classic for sure.\n\nI thought the relatively small main cast, as well as the single setting for the main plot, offered something we've been missing from films over the past few years; It wasn't overdone, with too many sub plots and settings that divert from the story, and in this case, the suspense of a horror/action- comedy. The lightness and comedy provided in dialogue, and the limited but amazing soundtrack, paired very well with the disturbing horror and action elements. I've only just started the novel this movie is based on, but so far, I can say the film has done a great job at adapting the story, and the actors did amazing in bringing David Koepp's characters to life.\n\nThis film offers suspense, wholesome romance, hilarious one-liners and an overall great viewing experience for those who enjoy action comedies and sci-fi horror. I can't recommend this film enough."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "92fe700b-621f-4a67-9148-c76749eabc6f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800971", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2d88eea1ee9c3feb1810983d7fad9a23324706ce5ca771042bfb55b209b49152"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "nicolasroop", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-17", "title": null, "content": "I'll admit, I'm partial to fun B-rated films. This one hits all the right notes with it's wacky fungus-among-us premise and it's gut busting gory bits.\n\nActingwise the film was perfect. For an action-horror-comedy hybrid the cast played all of their roles rather well and it was nice to Liam Neeson in a movie where his hammy delivery works in his favor. But the real star here was the FX team. From gruesome gory set pieces to some pretty cool zombie-like makeup, this film really hit those 80's notes well.\n\nIt's hard to call this a throwback film because of the setting but it certainly felt like one. Definitely a storyline that would have fit right in with the classics of cheesy 80's horror flicks.\n\nOverall, is it a modern day masterpiece? No. But in an age where most horror films seem to take itself a bit too seriously, it was refreshing to see something that decided to have a little fun for once. Honestly, might be the most fun horror film I've seen in theaters in quite. It had me laughing, gagging and cheering for the heroes! Highly recommended for a good time at the cinemas!\n\n4 flesh eating fungi out of 5."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "31a4c2ee-8917-484d-a6a5-9dae0620a637", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800971", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a0d4e93a9fd0d19cb823774fea273e143b8b7dc8226ca0dbf22cc8daaa55628d"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "paddy-89596", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-03-08", "title": null, "content": "There's suspending reality to enjoy a film and there's whatever this is. A dangerous mutating fungus that could kill all humanity is being kept next door to a storage unit and vast government facilities and equipment is behind a disused janitors door, or on other side of a single piece of plasterboard and some random insulation. The government couldn't spring for some concrete or impenetrable vault if it was that dangerous? This is outright stupid by all accounts!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "2f853af6-f453-4a4c-b4de-2fd3dc4e3e13", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800971", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "194efee8501b90720ab3a639f4201382a611ac40829b93ce967acbe2af680f08"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "masonsaul", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-22", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage never reaches the full potential that it's pretty gory horror comedy premise has but it always remains an entertaining watch which is comfortably sustained by a small cast and efficiently brief 99 minute run time. It intentionally runs on stupidity and negligence so it's impressive how this choice doesn't derail the film even when a couple of characters become increasingly annoying because of their really dumb decisions.\n\nJoe Keery makes a character whose constant need to talk could easily become annoying very endearing thanks to his likeability and Georgina Campbell is equally likeable as the more level headed one so their chemistry is suitably heartwarming which keeps things investing enough in between any gross or tense moments. Liam Neeson plays it straight with the odd bit of humour at the right time and he sells the seriousness of the situation.\n\nThe smaller budget is definitely felt in Jonny Campbell's direction thanks to an overuse of noticeably poor CGI for a lot of elements but he still does a good job by keeping the tone on point and delivering one particularly memorable suspenseful sequence. David Koepp's solid screenplay sets things up nicely whilst ensuring no joke massively overstays its welcome and reaches a satisfying conclusion as he adapts his own novel."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "cdafaefe-0461-4a42-aa06-bca0a42e1346", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800971", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "d8f8da72ba4750de8cd84d9613a1a3c0a183ffd78716bb050d531ef350916ef6"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "aronharde", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "This movie sounded exactly like my kind of film. Nothing too ambitious or overly artsy, just some dumb fun with decent production value. Cold Storage tells the story of Teacake, played by Joe Keery, and Naomi, played by Georgina Campbell, who work at a storage facility where a deadly fungus breaks out. The fungus infects people and animals and turns them into zombie like creatures. The two are supported by Liam Neeson as Robert Quinn, a government agent who is familiar with the fungus because of an incident from his past. There are a few additional characters, but the story mainly revolves around these three. All of the actors seem to be having fun and do a solid job bringing their characters to life.\n\nThe story is simple and anything but original, but I still enjoyed it. The storage facility is used effectively as the main setting, and I also liked the way the infected creatures were portrayed. The movie could have benefited from more practical effects, because much of the gore and many of the creature effects rely on digital work, which can look a bit weak at times in my opinion. Even so, the overall effects are still decent.\n\nThe film establishes its tone right away as goofy and far from serious. Personally, horror comedies do not work as well for me as they used to. That is probably because there are so many of them being released these days, and I am generally a tough audience when it comes to laughing at a screen. Even though the premise is clearly built around stupid fun, I would not have minded a slightly more serious tone with humor sprinkled throughout instead of a few scenes that feel almost like parody. That said, the tone is established early on, so it is a clear stylistic choice and I cannot criticize it too heavily.\n\nOverall, I had a good amount of fun with this movie and think it works well purely as entertainment. It will not win any major awards and probably will not show up on many top ten lists of the year, but it provides a fun and energetic 99 minutes including credits.\n\n[7,1/10]"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "1cc3e8c6-686d-4d78-89fe-a8b8c6c5218c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.800971", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ebbaf1a89898d5666f7516d48674f57d19848f60a3d4b3bf1faa28fb3ae36523"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "kosmasp", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-23", "title": null, "content": "No pun intended - we have a horror comedy that I reckon checks all the marks and goes more or less the route you'd expect it to go ... spreading around that is. That can be fun to watch too - which it is in this case.\n\nLikeable characters make you forget about holes in the story or any logic that may exist or not ... we'll put something up to cover it - that's how this works. Just don't overthink it ... and enjoy the quite brutal ride."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "25778313-4c29-4e9c-a69a-00a6ea0b173b", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "0452d8ed5b144af0d8f778774c78b16412fb398874b366669914a461c904d19f"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "sami2005", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage is a dull and uninspired film that quickly turns into a complete waste of time. The story feels recycled and predictable, repeating ideas that have already been used countless times in similar movies. There is very little originality, and the pacing drags without creating any real tension or excitement. The characters are thinly written, and the plot never develops into anything memorable. The only small reason to give it any credit at all is the presence of Liam Neeson, whose reputation alone adds a bit of curiosity. Even so, the film remains weak overall. Personally, I would rate it 1 out of 10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "cf283e8e-0e63-4e13-b32c-9a1f9ce636e9", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "d3205cdbf007f64030b2f4cade3c241d37fd9521866d9fa7765059f7da56b3bf"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "saolivaresm", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-09", "title": null, "content": "In Cold Storage, Jonny Campbell takes David Koepp's pen and transforms it into a play of light and shadow, where humor intertwines with the tremor of fear. The screen opens like an intimate stage, and there appear Joe Keery and Georgina Campbell, two figures who radiate complicity and invite us to accompany them on their delirious journey against a fungus that seems to sprout from the bowels of the unknown\n\nThe film breathes with the naturalness of a story told around a campfire: light, carefree, yet with enough tension to keep us engaged. Its spirit is reminiscent of Tremors, though without reaching the irreverent spark of that classic; here, the approach is simpler, more intimate, like a pastime to be enjoyed without pretensions.\n\nThe supporting cast-a surprisingly playful Liam Neeson and a Vanessa Redgrave who brings nobility and grace-enrich the narrative tapestry, transforming each scene into a mosaic of gestures and voices that complement each other harmoniously. The pacing flows seamlessly, the cinematography imbues the film with a vibrant feel, and the chemistry between the characters sustains the work like a firm bridge over turbulent waters.\n\nIt's not a film destined for posterity, but it is one of those charming pieces that linger in your memory as a fond recollection of a year in cinema. Cold Storage fulfills its purpose: to entertain, to seduce with its charisma, and to give us the feeling of having shared a pleasant time with characters who, more than heroes, seem like old friends."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "627da345-ab3d-4191-b926-d01572f77b7c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "82e97dfd114926fc6423a3e52ea3f9f8086bb15a1a115baf84a29bc607317195"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Pairic", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-22", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage: SciFi/Horror/Comedy film, while a strong line of black comedy runs through the movie it is not at all the comedy you might expect from the trailer. Actually it;s best to avoid the trailer as it gives too much away. In 1979 SkyLab burned up on re-entry, well no, an oxygen tank landed in Western Australia and was appropriated by a farmer who displayed it as a tourist attraction. Fast forward to 2005, when a Bio-Terror team reacts to strange reports, it turns out the tank contained a biological experiment involving fungus. It has now mutated and wiped out the inhabitants of the local hamlet. Quinn (Liam Neesin) one of the BioSoldiers survived but is injured, the area is immolated and the tank is brought to safe storage in Kansas. It's forgotten about when it's sub-basement repository is sealed off and the rest of the building is rented out to a storage unit company. 2023, we encounter some quirky characters working night shift at the facility, Teacake (Joe Keery) and Naomi (Georgina Campbell), hearing a beep and smashing walls and doors they find the tank. It has already leaked though so they can't be totally blamed for the mayhem which ensues. Quinn is alerted by a still working fail safe alarm but has difficulties getting the authorities to take things seriously. The fungus is evolving, turning people into zombies to spread, even making them explode. Also animals. Not nice to see an undead cat burst apart. Some real scenes of horror as the infection spreads, even a deer is contaminated in scenes which bring Train To Busan to mind. As well as the horror and comedy this is also an action thriller as the battle to stop the infection progresses. An interesting cameo by Vanessa Redgrave as an elderly customer who shoots a zombie. I wonder if this might have worked better without the comedy elements (I felt the same about Train To Busan), Directed by Jonny Campbell from a Screenplay by David Koepp based on the 2019 titular novel by Koepp. 7.5/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "d4502441-65e3-45fc-82ce-919f2fa1de36", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "446eacb58980fc3ae6d8376923e6b696db3a2b99c653c39c2b63c0d7ce179ddd"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "amrizzle", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-20", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage starts off reasonably well but quickly settles into a very familiar rhythm. Everything here has been seen before and while originality isn't always essential, there's nothing that really raises the pulse or sticks in the mind.\n\nThe filmmaking is competent. The sound mix is fine, the editing works in places but feels loose in others, and there are a few decent shots scattered throughout. Performances do the job without elevating the material.\n\nIt never becomes actively bad, but it never becomes exciting either. A perfectly serviceable movie that's easy to forget once it's over.\n\nFine as a switch off watch, but nothing more."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "934335fc-0dbf-4224-9c7d-102325c50a17", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "abd590f0ef6b806f1ea6cb0d7ebd6b5daaa14bbc1bca32680b4564468df8886d"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "theromanempire-1", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-23", "title": null, "content": "Really u have to see this in a theater so that u can enjoy one of the best, craziest ever black \"\"zombie\"\" comedies ever made.\n\nEspecially the opening was one of the best ever which nailed you to your seat.\n\nThen the movie had a 15-20 minutes kind ofa decline and boredoom but that did not last long and as we went in the last hour of the film things went crazy and the adrenalin was pumpin all over the place.\n\nNeeson delivered as always but also the rest of the cast were not bad at all.\n\nIf u liked similar films like \"black sheep\" and \"shaun of the dead\" then u must see \"cold storage\" too.\n\nGrade // 8 out of 10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "7a487888-c196-4082-b557-7337d9bd64f1", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "0eae6e038087c21ff3a9322b8e1677b7bfc46b1d995336822ff23d18014814a0"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "paulclaassen", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-08", "title": null, "content": "The Skylab space station fell out of orbit in 1979. During its mission, it had been home to hundreds of scientific experiments. Most of the debris burned up on re-entry, but some of it crashed to Earth. NASA thought it had recovered every piece. They were wrong.\n\nDr. Hero Martins from NASA and Major Robert Quinn arrive in a small Australian town following a call from a man saying everyone is dying. The bodies are found with their chests burst open. Dr Martins manages to get a sample from a highly infectious fungus, but gets infected in the process.\n\nThe sample is sent for analysis and kept in cold storage at a military facility. 18 Years later the underground facility is abandoned (but still monitored), and ground level is now a storage facility. Travis (nickname Teacake) works as a security guard and becomes curious when he hears a beeping sound. Fellow security guard Naomi is equally intrigued by the beeping, and suggests they break through the wall.\n\nThey discover the military facility and the fungus, and soon their lives are turned upside down as they fight for their lives. The fungus turns its victims into zombie-like beings determined to infect others. Naomi manages to call the authorities, and Quinn soon joins them in their fight against the fungus.\n\nThe initial mystery kept me on the edge of my seat, and I loved the unpredictability. Its like a zombie movie, but refreshingly different. This is an all-out fun and entertaining comedy horror that kept me smiling from beginning to end. I also adored the good - and funny - visual effects. Very entertaining indeed! I absolutely loved it!!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "16df4bca-150d-4603-8e0f-7ccee1ae86d4", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c2de5d03d49e819bb4e7d75b72d0ec79846d01d31cd6762492fe46f8caa56d8c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Alba90", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-03-08", "title": null, "content": "The whole thing feels weirdly artificial, like the script was stitched together by AI. It's boring, nothing feels special, and I rolled my eyes more times than I can count. Every single person act stupid, otherwise we couldn't have a movie.\n\nThe acting is just bad. Georgina Campbell really got on my nerves, her performance felt stiff and distracting. And Liam Neeson basically shows up as a parody version of his Taken persona.\n\nThe directing is messy, the tone is all over the place, and even the fungus, doesn't behave consistently. It just does whatever the plot needs at the moment.\n\nThe random love story was so unnecessary and awkward, ugh.\n\nHonestly, I want those minutes of my life back. I wish I could unsee it."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "32ae5d36-c5a1-4c28-b289-7232a7d97e5c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ff23645d9da2efaa5c9a044d5014460aab5d6cda2cce03e74cb1efd3ad8c559c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Miguel1226", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-17", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage is a solid, well-paced sci-fi thriller that succeeds largely because of its concept and visual execution.\n\nThe central threat is compelling, and the contained setting keeps tension consistent throughout. The pacing is steady and avoids dragging, which helps maintain engagement.\n\nWhere the film falls slightly short is in its character development. While the performances are serviceable, the characters don't stand out in a way that elevates the material. Even so, the movie remains entertaining and visually effective."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "66fb6b81-15c9-4e0f-92c6-844e9fa7b127", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2feef9975a133ad90bd9a506b90c5483bf06fb71b42799583999903982a6b2c2"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Rastl-7", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-18", "title": null, "content": "Too many horror movies these days try to slow burn the horror part (imo) while this one does a strong lead up, gives you the premise, slows enough to introduce the characters, then puts the pedal to the metal.\n\nNothing in this movie is original but it's been blended in a way that's refreshingly enjoyable. The characters are divided into \"smart enough not to do stupid things\", \"do stupid things so they get what they deserve\", and one poor \"wrong place, wrong time\".\n\nThe one quibble I have is the very end scene. It answers a question from earlier that the audience may have been forgotten but in a slapstick way that doesn't fit the rest of the tone of the movie."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "5d2f8351-dea0-49d8-84d5-e5130084f7a3", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "013737a3e1ea89350926ebbae2fd0b77542c129f06303719cfd29ad7027c0359"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "movieman6-413-929510", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-09", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage is a new science-fiction horror comedy directed by Jonny Campbell, known for directing several episodes of TV series such as Dracula (2020) and Westworld.\n\nTravis \"Teacake\" Meacham (Joe Keery) and Naomi Williams (Georgina Campbell) are both young employees at a storage facility. The company is located on a site that was formerly an American military base.\n\nWhen a parasitic fungus becomes active again, the employees must try to contain it within the facility and prevent it from spreading, until former bioterrorism agent Robert Quinn (Liam Neeson) arrives to render the fungus inactive once more.\n\nThe film comes across as an entertaining science-fiction horror comedy in which the characters must prevent the spread of a fungal infection. When infected, victims turn into brainless zombies who actively try to spread the fungus further. As a result, the film feels like a mix of the series The Last of Us (due to the dangerous fungus) and the film Slither (because of its horror-comedy tone). However, the comedy can occasionally feel a bit weak.\n\nAlthough David Koepp, the writer of both the script and the novel, conceived and wrote the story during the COVID-19 period-wondering what the life of someone like a security guard or retail worker might be like-the film still brings those themes to mind. This is especially noticeable for cinephiles or fans of films, TV series, or video games. There are also elements in the film that may unintentionally reference these ideas.\n\nThe visual effects are less convincing compared to those in larger films or TV series, but they fortunately work well for the film's comedic aspect. Explosions or infected creatures can even come across as humorous. The use of CGI or green screen is often noticeable.\n\nThe cast portrays their roles in a believable and fitting way. Joe Keery and Georgina Campbell work well as storage facility employees who take little pleasure in their jobs but have their own reasons for staying. Out of boredom, they wander through suspicious storage areas, leading to the discovery of the fungus. Liam Neeson plays more in the background, providing explanations and instructions to the duo. Instead of his former action-hero roles, he now contributes more on a comedic level."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "ce484422-3ed6-4850-b7dd-92a737e46f2c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c89d43b03e7bf763c356df9e3a3509b42d9606db2481591862b5c5f03239515f"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "eve_dolluk", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-06", "title": null, "content": "Not a bad watch, leave your brain at home and just enjoy the show type of movie.\n\nIts all a bit tongue in cheek and while its mot laugh out loud comedy its amusing.\n\nA green space fungus travels back to earth on a decommissioned space station. The fungus infects the host until eventually they explode.\n\nThink of something a bit like The Thing but more in your face with the same level of stomach churning gore.\n\nOverall the FX were good and well produced.\n\nLiam Neeson plays the military man in a similar style to Frank Drebin.\n\nJoe Keery and Naomi Williams are the young nighy shift storage workers who get caught up in the whole mess.\n\nEven Vanessa Redgrave makes a small pointless appearance ( i wonder what happended to her ?? )\n\nMost of the film makes little sense and there are lots of moments where you have to suspend disbelief, its designed for the teen weekend cinema goer.\n\nIts dumb and fun\n\n6/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "0702130b-6a54-4c9a-9d25-d1cd89aad8b4", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "f2b237ad2440a481ebc878414331ffa83c1abbbe704378926a2620c271d872a8"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "ThereelscoopwithKK", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage might be one of the best movies I've seen in the very specific category of mindless, silly, self-aware, B-movie horror-comedies. I mean this to be a compliment. But at the same time my score of 9/10 is based on judging this movie against others in its weight class per se. It is not to suggest it's truly up there with the all time greatest movies.\n\nAnyways, the premise of Cold Storage is extremely simple and one we've all encountered before. A fungal outbreak spreads and creates a mess that needs containing. But the movie executes it so cleanly that the simplicity becomes a strength rather than a flaw. It never pretends to be smarter than it is, yet it still manages to keep real stakes alive amid all the chaos.\n\nThe film strikes that tricky balance most horror/comedies miss. It doesn't take itself too seriously, but it takes itself just seriously enough. There's just enough serious tension when there needs to be and then it pivots right back to absurdity without losing the story.\n\nJoe Keery basically feels like he's channeling a slightly older version of Steve from Stranger Things, but this time dropped into a shady storage facility instead of an ice cream shop or video store . He once again nails that sweet spot with a combination of sarcasm, charm, and the occasional serious urgency. The writers also managed to get the most out of his skill set by landing the jokes at the right time.\n\nComedy-horror's must always walk a tightrope. Go too goofy and nothing matters. Go too serious and the thin premise collapses. Cold Storage threads that needle better than most.\n\nThis isn't a movie that's going to stimulate the intellectual parts of your brain, but it's the kind of movie you throw on to escape for 90 minutes and just have fun.\n\nIt's the perfect late night, cheap-ticket, \"$5 Tuesday in February\" kind of watch.\n\nIt's barely being marketed, but if you're burnt out and just want something dumb, funny, and entertaining in the best possible way, this one's an easy recommendation."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "a71c70d6-edd2-4f0c-93af-766a63b78daa", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "b4ef363f9c48a57c3d51a0baa62e7d230876177ad11faad3bbc4f072d63e8078"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "AndreaS-3148", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "If u have seen the trailer you have seen the Movie, don't waste any more minutes of your life on this movie.\n\nAm just using up words here to fill the allotted character requirement which again is another complete waste of time... So if ur still here I will say again, do not waste time on this movie!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "1c05463f-3ce6-459a-af5e-e34b8e1ef916", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2d0b56ec6426fddec53237e7f385e382942c8294560f5bb6faafbfa17e3ce090"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "southdavid", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-02", "title": null, "content": "A long cinema day came to an end with my favourite of the three I saw that day. A gory, surprisingly low budget feeling comedy horror, that succeeds on strength of performance.\n\nIntrigued by a distant alarm, self-storage workers Naomi (Georgina Campbell) and Travis (Joe Keery) discover hidden rooms in their building. They learn that the site used to belong to the army, and that a fungal virus, that was stored there, has breached its containment. The breach activates Robert Quinn (Liam Neeson), a C. I. A specialist, who has experience with the fungus previously and who understands the risks, if the virus gets out.\n\nI'm an old school \"Evil Dead\" / \"Dawn of the Dead\" fan, so am usually in the bag for a gory horror film. \"Cold Storage\" does follow in those fine traditions. The budget is not massive, but what has been spent on a mixture of practical and CGI effects has been done effectively. What's absolutely key to the films success though is the casting. There are two key relationships that the film hinges on. The one between Georgina Campbell and Joe Keery and the one between Liam Neeson and Lesley Manville. Both are note perfect. Keery in particular carries much of the film and it's not an exaggeration to say that it wouldn't have worked at all, if that performance was judged incorrectly. It is strange to see so much talent from the UK in what is an American film (albeit one filmed mostly in Italy). It's unusual to see Lesley Manville in a genre film, and six time Oscar nominee Vanessa Redgrave, presumably drawn in by the chance to see her son-in-law, though the don't share any scenes. The film also has a small but key role for Aaron Heffernan and a single scene on for Daniel Rigby.\n\nAdmittedly, it's not super original. It's Zombie movie tropes are present, including a biker gang, like the aforementioned \"Dawn of The Dead\" and there's not actually that much plot overall to concern yourself with.\n\nA really fun B movie."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "24ed3dfe-cf94-4026-bc71-4c79b0ed1083", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "40144c95f9f375109c5d03a89c5446a1eeb0411fe642aba5f70195cc019ece8a"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "TheFilmDetective", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-21", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage is an exhilarating, pulse-pounding ride that combines the best elements of this gore fest sci-fi horror. It's a pretty smart script, and some good acting performances, and its visually striking direction make it a standout in a crowded genre. Cold Storage is about the cost of its scientific ambition and the danger of playing god and with nature. The movie delves deep into themes of unchecked progress and the unintended consequences of tampering with the natural world. It raises thought provoking questions about ethics in science and corporate mistakes and the chaos it can bring .\n\nThe film might be too intense for some viewers who don't like blood and vomit but for fans of cerebral thrillers and horror sci fi then cold storage is a must watch for you .While I did enjoy this movie its not perfect and won't break many records at the box office,but there was a few pacing issues towards the middle of the film which did slightly disrupt the tension and the storyline .\n\nBut in all honesty it wasn't that bad and was worth the watch."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "7d57450c-2a26-45d0-a53f-e62eff865434", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e1f00f51ed19062d232497a66e90640808f15ac6b377122bb751420b26f59a08"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "DoNotComeToTheCinemaDepressed", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-23", "title": null, "content": "Just Got Out Of a Screening of Cold Storage.\n\n1. It's Exactly What you would expect, 2. It does it well, and 3. It's a good time at the cinema.\n\nMore things I liked about the Film -\n\n\ud83d\udcc3 - The Dialogue Between Teacake and Naomi was Really Good to Listen to and Watch as they Interact With Eachother.\n\n\ud83c\udf89 - The Overall Tone of the Film is Just Fun, with witty moments sprinkled in. Moments from Neeson, moments with that Biker Gang near the End, and Moments with Neesons Friend Trini.\n\n\u23f3 - The Film Doesn't overstay it's welcome, it's a tight 90 Minute Film. It gets in, does a thing well and gets out.\n\nSo Overall, it's a 10(To Scale) From Me."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "af57dfff-ef7e-480d-aabd-5c71cf2e7744", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "7a3b4893e0c4739876e8ccb4112ab983d5e30165c9f73115af28ccddabc3098e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "eternitycomplex", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-03-09", "title": null, "content": "People have such varying tastes... I'm shocked to see some of the bad reviews.\n\nDefinitely one of the better movies I've seen in several years. A screenplay by a tried and tested (and talented) screenwriter goes a long way. The jokes landed for me. Interesting and amusing characters. A solid pace throughout without painful filler.\n\nAbsurd at times without being TOO absurd. Serious at times but with out being TOO serious. It just landed in a perfect sweet spot for me. That's really all I can say."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "9dbec191-0c47-4fd5-8346-bd095aa23bdc", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.801482", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "6ffa5a4a1ec9847023d14083d3ffa89b8307201cd37675681f47b52374fe2a59"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "VictoriaTamar", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-10", "title": null, "content": "Going into this is knew I would have the hibby g-bies from watching the trailer. After finishing the film, I have to say it was a fun thrill ride that sweetly superimposes romance with fungal horror and action sequences. I REALLY like this, it was definitely gore filled and was almost too much for my squeamish self. The acting was good, and the plot was a mix of horror, action, romance,gruesome gore and comedy. I'd definitely recommend!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "836c0c17-eddf-4d37-a6d3-8919aaa5d388", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "01b50528322f20fd5c848b27b7c3bba0e963bf7d9045de89127b5f5bb077a4cf"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "ycgpwydjj", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-15", "title": null, "content": "Truly had a blast with this film this is one of those movies you can watch over and over again and never get bored .definitely a campy horror comedy at heart but this cast and script make it one of the most enjoyable and entertaining films i've seen in a very long time kerry and campbell are a blast to watch . Fun time and money well spent . Recommend if you like campy zombie outbreak films . Kerry and campbell make this movie shine ."}}
