{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "9a00bff6-2e73-4b50-9e2c-3d5474fa885d", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "87bc80362cb2b690cc6fb39547898323259a9d3def009140593f151127a647b9"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "lord_orsum", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-26", "title": null, "content": "None of this movie makes sense, and that is fine. A mutated fungus from SkyLab crashes to earth 18 years ago carrying a mutated fungus. The military manage to contain it, but keep a sample, stick it in storage and then completely forget about it.\n\nThe military storage is now a commercial self-storage business and the fungus has escaped. Bad things ensure.\n\nThe lead characters are surprisingly likeable, and do not do anything particularly stupid (I was especially pleased that they were not responsible for the fungus escape). Liam Neeson plays up his tough guy persona - he appears to be slipping into self-parody at this stage of his career.\n\nIt is all B-movie zombie nonsense, but highly enjoyable."}}
