{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "d1019869-74df-49cd-a855-c83fc258efc0", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "731b416054e15f0bc3827fc9f7923bc124753c8d5651b335698c489df831a5b4"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "EmilyD-6875", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-15", "title": null, "content": "I watched the movie today on valentine's day (not relevant for the review lol) but I really loved the movie. I initially wanted to watch the movie for Joe Keery, but I ended up loving it. The movie has the perfect combination of reaction, I jumped, I laughed and I sat on the edge of my seat at times."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "03ed542d-0ee8-4d0d-afce-559bd266640e", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2bce8d3d856b3d2d15f2e03a45fee2909cf80703951050d3ad8cd5403e3d4b9c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "capybarus", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-08", "title": null, "content": "The movie is entertaining enough and characters are all vibrant. The movie has a few other interesting subplots besides the toxic fungus story line, e.g. An older generation bailing out the careless modern days and individual responsibility vs incompetent leadership. Visually the movie is very good. Morally the movie is really clean - the bad guys get what they deserve and all good guys survive. My only gripe is that they put too many encounters between the good guys and the fungus where the splatter unrealistically keeps missing them. I know it would not have made cinematic sense to have suited the characters in haz mat outfits for the entire movie, but at least they could have staged the splatter scenes a bit more meticulously."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "97567594-7d57-46be-983b-b5d538da8ff0", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "0a2fa3c6ff13a36527899b98b9a34c25b5e8e573cb44da1d06de40bf02d2005f"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "iamgrebo", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-20", "title": null, "content": "Just out of seeing this in the cinema and I can't remember watching a film with so much humour and jump scares. Liam Neeson was perfect for the role. A fully enjoyable movie. It had action, humour and a fun story very remincent of the 80s Sci-fi horror movies.\n\nA fully enjoyable movie fun for all the family \u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50\u2b50"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "476eefbf-a556-4a3d-9f59-ab27bb8b35b4", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "67f76a6c1c5ebde09feb87f8ec9c648fef04e2b7c205fe542e0dfa3b067caa07"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "jboothmillard", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-28", "title": null, "content": "I watched the trailer for this zombie-themed comic scary movie only a few days before its release; the star of Taken made it appealing, and I thought it might be fun, so I went to see it, directed by Jonny Campbell (Alien Autopsy, Dracula). Basically, in 1979, space station Skylab was decommissioned through atmospheric re-entry, but an oxygen tank survived and landed in Western Australia. In 2005, biochemist Dr. Hero Martins (Smile's Sosie Bacon, daughter of Kevin Bacon and Kyra Sedgwick) joins Pentagon bioterror operatives Robert Quinn (Liam Neeson) and Trini Romano (Lesley Manville) to find the tank, which was taken by a farmer and made into a makeshift Skylab museum. Investigating the tank, it is found to have been carrying an infectious fungus for study whilst in space. Days before the arrival of the three scientists, the farmer attempted to clean the tank, causing the fungus to mutate, infect the farmer, and kill him and many people in the surrounding area. The infected corpses are found to have exploded from the inside. Martins takes a sample of the fungus, unaware that she stepped on corrosive ground, allowing the fungus to attach to the boots of her hazmat suit. The fungus breaks through the boots, infects Martins and starts controlling her activities; realising she is infected, Martins commits suicide. The military incinerates the farm and the corpses while the sample is taken to an underground cold storage vault at the Atchison Storage Facility in Kansas. Through the years, the government has sealed the vault and rented the ground-level section to a self-storage company. In the present day, Travis \"Teacake\" Meacham (Joe Keery) works as a night security guard at the storage facility, along with new recruit Naomi (Barbarian's Georgina Campbell). That night, elderly client Mary Rooney (Vanessa Redgrave) enters her storage unit intent on committing suicide. Soon, Travis hears a beeping alarm coming from somewhere, and Naomi joins him to try to discover its source. Breaking through a thin wall, they find large servers from the past, and the beeping is an alert for a malfunction in the vault's systems caused by a rise in temperatures. The alert prompts Rober, living in Raleigh, North Carolina, to be contacted by a military officer, only identifying herself as \"Abigail\" (Ellora Torchia). Knowing the dangers brought by the fungus, which is already breaking out of the vault, Robert asks the military for transportation. Arriving in Kansas, he reunites with Trini, who drives him to her home, where she has a device they require. Travis and Naomi explore further behind the broken wall, finding a hatch leading down further into the facility, and heading down a tunnel to discover the sealed vault. Outside the door, they find hundreds of infected rats and a rapidly growing fungus trying to break out. Meanwhile, on the surface outside the facility entrance, Naomi's ex-boyfriend Mike Snyder (Aaron Heffernan) arrives in his car; he has Naomi's cat dead in the trunk. A cockroach infected by the fungus has made its way through the various air vents and passages of the facility to reach the surface and enter the car trunk to infect the dead cat and revive it. Once Mike lets the revived cat out, it kills itself, impaling its head on an antenna, spreading remains that infect both Mike and a deer. Returning to the ground level, Travis and Naomi see Mike and the deer have entered. While the deer enters the elevator and eventually swells and explodes, an infected Mike pursues them to spread the fungus. Travis and Naomi hide in one of the storage units, and when Mike walks away, they call the military. Abigail redirects them to Robert, who tells them that he is on his way and advises them to stay hidden. However, manager Griffin (Gavin Spokes) arrives with a gang of bikers to take smuggled televisions from storage. Realising Griffin and the gang have entered, Travis and Naomi leave their hiding spot to warn them. But Griffin ignores their warnings, and Mike attacks and infects the gang members. Mike approaches Travis and Naomi, but they are saved by Mary, who kills him with a shotgun. They get outside and find Robert, who gives them a bomb to be lowered and placed outside the vault door to destroy the whole facility from within and eliminate any trace of the fungus. As the duo place the bomb, killing one of the infected along the way, Robert kills one of the infected bikers trying to escape. The encounter causes Robert to fall on his back and find himself unable to get up. Griffin has made his way outside and tries to steal Robert's car keys when an arriving Trini kills him. Robert has warned that the bomb will detonate in fifteen minutes, but the timer is damaged, and the countdown is seen glitching and changing constantly, meaning the detonation may occur sooner. Travis and Naomi reach the surface and carry Robert into Trini's car, and they drive away moments before the bomb explodes. Days later, Travis is spending time with Naomi and her daughter (twins Vanessa and Valentina Popkova), and he explains the reason for his nickname \"Teacake\". Robert is recovering in the hospital and watches a television news report praising him for preventing the outbreak while condemning the military for nearly causing it. A visiting Abigail, whose real name is Ishani, admits that she leaked Robert's reports on the fungus to the press. The final moment sees the facility being decommissioned, while another infected deer is seen nearby, meaning the fungus could spread again. Also starring Darrell D'Silva as The Rev, Daniel Rigby as Anthony, Rob Collins as Enos Minjarra, Andrew Brooke as Greg, Richard Brake as Jerabek, Andrew Brooke as Ironhead, Lujza Richter as Garbage, Nahel Tzegai as Cuba, and Justin Salinger as Dr. Friedman. Neeson plays another tough operative well, Keery and Campbell are fine, and Manville and Baco have their moments. It has all the right ingredients: a deadly virus turning victims into zombies, with nods to George A. Romero's \"living dead\" films and some amusingly gnarly violence and gore; I found it a bit predictable most of the time, and it could have been both scarier and funnier, but it's not a bad comedy horror. Worth watching!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "3035bd5c-e5c7-4524-b5e6-b92ae932cb3b", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "fbc3d6b98179d6dd4f10a7166d8bcd2435446eff04b9fc31c03b4a127a13a768"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "nickywinchesters", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-24", "title": null, "content": "The family and I really enjoyed the movie, the main cast is excellent, Joe Keery is such a scene stealer, delivered a wonderful performance, his comedic timing and delivery is so good, Georgina Campbell was excellent too, her character was fun to watch, and as always Liam Neeson is a legend. Overall a great entertaining movie!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "573b3edd-5cd2-49d2-ab17-0bd1bd0e5718", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "6d72692a1c30f6f72b9b9cff0d7bb2bb3d284af0573a9e6cb0987af7751e0d63"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "HalphStaph", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-21", "title": null, "content": "The casting was fabulous - each role was portrayed to perfection. Definitely brings a lot of \"But how... Why.... Huh?\" questions, yet I expressly got the feeling that was intended.\n\nWell done on the sets, FX makeup and digital effects were above par - cringe worthy, which is hard to accomplish these days.\n\nDefinitely feel the concept will release another film, possibly a sequel or another in the same world with similar circumstances but perhaps a larger response with a \"protagonist\" that doesn't care if you send one or five hundred.., it won't be enough. And I'm certainly dusting off the Emergency bunker architectural plans!\n\nEnjoy the flick, it is a dusty bucket of fun and thought provoking entertainment."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "61b413da-829f-4722-8f77-f0cf288037c7", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a939d88782f2f3707042046d93f07e871be369a2bbc5399551f9a4e879ff8c7b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "sierbahnn", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-08", "title": null, "content": "This is well-acted, superbly casted and has a great mix of cgi and practical effects, prosthetics and makeup to make it look well rounded. It is a fun movie, with good dialogue, characters you get invested in, and a plot that feels urgent. I recommend this a lot, and with Liam delivering his lines perfectly you get the icing on the cake!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "30f89d1f-c200-48d5-9f02-2d8be4bff639", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "db07acec4b1b33b2c5b736516612fe0fd3277eb91b25ffced5733531c6287785"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "MudarrabA", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-18", "title": null, "content": "Honestly I Enjoyed this movie a lot. And ofc i am just here for Joe Kerry one of my fav actor. The movie is purely fun. Everything is just perfect pacing acting. I highly recommded to all watch this movie. Bez this movie provide best exprience of movie bez no timepass just stick to plot. Some plot give you rest otherwise whole movie is just like wow what going onn here."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "ed7b1318-0b9d-4a8d-9168-fb617ccb054d", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "056ce12c98a939017dc3773ac608cfc7f493cf7cdf682e8205887bd7157b3d10"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "SnoopyStyle", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-09", "title": null, "content": "In 1979, Skylab crashes onto the Australian outback. Some time later, an experiment starts leaking and a fungus wipes out the locals. Robert Quinn (Liam Neeson) is one of a scientists sent to investigate. They end up burning out the entire community and keep a small sample in a military storage site. Years go by and the site is decommissioned. The fungus remains and the site is turned into private storage.\n\nThe premise is iffy. I don't hold the military bureaucracy in the highest light, but this is too stupid even for that. As for the two explosions, they really need to add the big mushroom clouds. Beside the logic of the big heat, it is visually arresting and that's useful. Finally, I kept wondering if they're going bring out the flamethrowers. Guns are fun, but this situation really requires fire. The two civilians are doing some dumb stuff although that is the genre. This is goo-splattering fun, but it can't be taken seriously."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "03987456-0ddf-49d3-928b-f2b672d43ff5", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "1bf29ff256dd75fd459f86d713c4d0d3f6505d6d5259040ddf7b9b2719940535"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "skylerkennethkidd", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-17", "title": null, "content": "Its funny, but not a pure comedy. However others found it funnier than me. Breakout of parasitic fungus turning people and animals into zombie like exploders. Non of it is to be taken seriously and the story line is very loose in seriousness. However, entertaining. Ive also seen alot worse movies so because of this it still hits that 7 mark for me.\n\nWatched at AMC on 2-16-2026."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "472e1b72-1433-4726-b875-bb64c2e779ba", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "20fef0caa33b3613c3121aff4e74665939798a7807d1837d5a5d153e1f95cb11"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "DOWNRIVERREVIEW", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-21", "title": null, "content": "So I was excited to see this. You got the stranger things star Joe Kerry and taken star liam Neeson combining for a Sci fy film. Everything about that sounded great. I just finished it an it felt it lacked in a few areas but overall its worth a watch. It's not something your gonna come out the theater and give 10 stars but I'd say a solid 6 and a half or 7 is a reasonable number on this film."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "5d68ab52-8409-46c7-9e4f-486ace5fd50b", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "d0510983ef4e4d8b8e720a1cf236ab7249163c3f651a0fa98f46612af7872d3e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "ops-52535", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-03-11", "title": null, "content": "Action to the last splitsecond on an atomic electrode jump that emits light and energy, so the E. T wont phone homia anymore...\n\nthis is real fungiifastfood for every vegetarian out there, and for all of us that devoured scifi in the 1970's and 80's. Its a light story so the median jane and joe may hang in there, and its filled with well exagerated detonation countdown action that emits light and coloured flames through your brains...\n\nand it even has an happy ending after cooling down overheating brainboddies in a war of the worlds, pretty gory moments here and there, that may avert some and retain others...\n\nbut my alpha omega message is that fun-gus is actually fun stuff, a big recommend from the grumpy old man..."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "4f127c16-1f3a-4622-970f-7001f07877b8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "4326a842f7f64e7e3987fc3d468dc183e32ada2619df2c104542776116dc41ea"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "erdodo", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-03-09", "title": null, "content": "The 2026 film Cold Storage is truly a masterpiece of the comedy horror genre. Without exception, every actor plays their role perfectly. And that's exactly what makes a good film, among other things. Although it's a B-movie, it could easily pass for a normal A-movie.\n\nThis film is not to be missed. ."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "5d2da75a-04a7-4bf8-b289-4314c35c700d", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "3cf8ae0b36f504bbfdb0bf02da9acd721d681362fd9e16613871c07adafa16a1"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "chand-suhas", "rating": 4, "date": "2026-03-10", "title": null, "content": "NASA were wrong yet again, when their decommissioned space station Skylab entered earth's atmosphere in 1979, precisely in Western Australia. A fungal outbreak happens in 2007 and it got contained by Trini Romano and Robert Quinn, with the sample being transported to an underground cold storage in Kansas. Fast forward to the current time, the building is rented out to a storage company. The fungus as expected successfully breaches the cold storage. It is upto the storage unit night guards Naomi Williams and Travis Meacham to survive the night while Robert and Trini are called upon to handle the situation.\n\nDavid Koepp's screenplay oversimplifies the narrative, focusing on the humor. The tone is set early on and the narrative driven entirely by it's humor, needed it's characters to be used in a better way. The runtime is perfect yet the humor was largely miss than hits. It was not meant to be taken seriously but as the timeline jumped from 1979 to current times, the director throws in an infected rat king, a revived cat, a deer and one Mike, before introducing a biker gang. The set up was there for a crazy sci-fi horror comedy but somehow it all felt just not enough. The conveniently written screenplay fails to captivate on Naomi and Travis's \"accidental\" survival instincts. Compared to them, Robert and Trini had more effective chemistry in terms of fun banter. Overall, it was a missed opportunity."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "cc31c1b1-ed6a-408b-b481-32b42d7050d7", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "90fb35df748be92b0ed3c179ce7e7e63015bf4616420d021b902e69756d8bfe1"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "searlesk", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-03-08", "title": null, "content": "It was a pretty decent movie. I like Liam neeson which is what drew me to the movie in the first place. The other actors were also very good and told a great story. IT has a few holes in the plots but still a pretty decent watch. They try to keep it serious with a few jokes that aspect alone keeps the plot on track."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "bb983a62-ca9b-471b-9c0e-7dcf464eb306", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "28433ea58eebd6a9569695143b0210ae219c5cc7558c28b4d409ed1af1737162"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "daisukereds", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-11", "title": null, "content": "Deadly Fungus that came from space is stored somewhere to prevent it from spreading. Couple of years later its storage stops working! Now, a couple of involved civilians and a retired Government agent get on it.\n\nIt is a perfectly fine and enjoyable film, with decently charming characters. The pacing is good and the threat very well done. There are cheap-looking CGI scenes at times.. but it knows to be brief and have a somewhat satisfying ending.\n\nI mean... it was o-kay. Felt like one of this direct to DVD films from the 2000s."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "36a7ed8e-dad7-451b-8ac3-c476ab34c060", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "dbd3f16649829814211a741c3e58c8e8467bd8f88dd070aac49e1716130e5153"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "TyraI-1", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-24", "title": null, "content": "The film was brilliant, had a great story line (I actually have never read the book). It made me want to read the book at least.\n\nI feel like the ending was a bit rushed, after Teacake (Joe Keery) got shot in the arm, the ending was a big push to 'getting it over with' in the end which I was a bit disappointed about.\n\nHowever it's witty, comical, and keeps you on edge. Has the right amount of jumpy parts and jokey gore.\n\nAlso anything Joe Keery is in, turns to gold.\n\nTeacake had crispy hair, an earring and a dream."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "2f49a3cc-6a5f-4a42-83e9-b985848caca6", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "572779ad5b49eaccf91f1b71c93ff5988b5ba9fbbe2beb5d1d5750bb1d026479"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Amy-027", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-21", "title": null, "content": "Really enjoyed it!! Liam Neeson was great. The storyline and sfx was great. Can be quite gory at some points though. Hopefully Joe Keery lands more acting jobs in the future. He's a very underrated actor.\n\nThe only thing I feel let this film down was the marketing. Online, I barely seen any trailers for it. There wasn't even any film posters advertising it in my cinema.\n\nOverall, it was a great film. Definitely worth seeing!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "6ee2470a-7a60-4dc7-9565-e14f3ebfc052", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "20e1265abad5526c8ab0a52808be4e9049325638576bf0df5dc17066fa94722c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "destroyerwod", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-10", "title": null, "content": "So when i watched the trailer i was expecting some goofy B level horror comedy and its like the movie never truly commited to it. Like sure some parts are and yes there is some absurde story parts in there where you think \"yeah obviously the USA governement wouldn't had done that...well pre 2024 at least...\".\n\nBut overall i think the movie took too much time to get going. You have the intro wich is fine, but then it takes forever to get going with the 2 leads discovering the virus. If you gonna do some fungus that can control humans and animals... go balls to the walls and make it funnier? I dunno.\n\nWhat saved the movie for me was the chemistry and interactions between the 2 leads wich was good and interesting. Both actors develivered well and were likeable. Liam Neeson and his other side character counterpart were funny at times too but while i expected him to be \"in the crisis\" quite early, you realize he spend 3 quarter of the movie getting \"there\" and thats where the part about \"the movie going too slow\" kinda hit for me.\n\nI mean, what i expected was 2 young random employees discover a \"virus\", Liam Neeson in super governement agent mode show up after like 20 minutes, save them, then we have a movie about them surviving and containing it. It was not that.\n\nIt seem to take too long til the crazy stuff happen and while the build up is not bad per say due to the good performances of the actors, it just kinda feel like it take too long for a movie that is only 90 minutes or so.\n\nAbout the special effects and gore, well while some of the VFX are good, some felt clearly CGI, yet the movie never felt \"cheap\" per say, so it had a decent production quality and didn't felt too much like a B movie.\n\nOverall my feeling is that it was not bad, but it could had been so much more. Its like it couldn't decide between being serious and going full on dark horror comedy.\n\nSo yeah its ...fine. Its enjoyable. But it won't be some cult classic like you wanna go back and show your friends. 6 out of 10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "fac50e8a-a1ed-43d2-82af-9e68580ef635", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e420aa86a63c6914efb91cd646442547ca44d5eb567ac1c997fa1576472ddcc1"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "LucasJ-774", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-24", "title": null, "content": "This was a blast to watch. The use of horror and comedy was used amazingly. Joe keery was my favourite as he made me laugh multiple times. This film was a fun watch!\n\nIt was a fun concept and it was well executed. All the cast was funny to watch. A film which I would definitely watch again when I get the chance."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "2c523659-536b-47ce-a44b-9abfc206c916", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ac21c2e8fa57c0fe62f3a908c60c892e5727a21849dcf8dac8c4a66bfd3c079d"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Christian2Cole", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "Casting was good, however, I'd of been curious as to who could have brought a more accurate representation \"old soldier\" with just a touch more of action. Nonetheless, you get all bases covered with this one. I'd say credit to the writers as the character development was as swift as the spread of the fungus. And yet, still affective. Let's be honest, who doesn't want to see characters make bad choices when they truly deserve the consequences. Finally, I'm impressed with how they packed so much of the right elements in a movie that never had a dull moment.\n\nI enjoyed it."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "588bf649-6ed1-4f57-9be9-c64c1ff65bdd", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ac3c0c79405775adc0fe282bd78d4d0962afe8617ebe212ac4f354d205cd027b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Stanlee107", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-10", "title": null, "content": "Having seen the trailer for *Cold Storage*, I was curious enough to give it a shot. Within minutes I was playing a game of \"Hey, I know that person!\"-there's Liam Neeson, Joe Keery (aka Steve from *Stranger Things*), and Georgina Campbell from *Barbarian*. Not a bad trio to anchor what is essentially a gooey creature feature.\n\nThe premise is gloriously simple: a deadly green alien organism that assimilates humans and animals, spreading its DNA like the universe's worst flu. Naturally, it's locked away in-you guessed it-cold storage. And naturally, two curious employees, Teacake (Keery) and Naomi (Campbell), decide to go check things out just as the organism is attempting its escape. What could possibly go wrong?\n\nMeanwhile, Liam Neeson shows up as Robert Quinn, a covert government agent who has already seen what these things can do and would very much prefer not to relive the experience. Neeson mostly does his usual gravelly \"I'm tired of this nonsense\" routine, which honestly works.\n\nThe film feels like a throwback to late-90s or early-2000s sci-fi thrillers Hollywood doesn't really make anymore. It leans into dark humour, ridiculous deaths, and obvious nods to classics like *Mars Attacks!*.\n\nIs it groundbreaking? Not even slightly. Is it fun, weird, and occasionally very silly? Absolutely. Worth a watch if you're in the mood for nostalgic B-movie chaos."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "16a2b116-bdeb-4009-8950-681e7d9e409f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "071110e05ac7e63128caf1349db9bc9998070484efa0cceab2df3869b77a4771"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "Ice_2", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-23", "title": null, "content": "We never have movies like these anymore, an original si-fi movie at your local theaters. Every time you look at what movies are playing none really suit your likings or are just trash sequels. It's fun to go to the movies and see a fast paced funny, entertaining and, overall good movie. The movie \"Cold Storage\" knows exactly what it wants to be and delivers a fast paced regular workers to now save the world workers. The movie follows Teacake {Travis Meacham} (Played by Joe Keery) and Naomi Williams (Played by Georgina Campbell) as they are both struggling with bad decisions that ended up at this job. We get a back story on the fungus as we follow Robert Quinn (Played by Liam Neeson) I like how the story shifts and we get a backstory onto the fungus on how it started. This isn't a typical \"Need brains\" zombie fungus, it's very accurate biologically, look, i'm not a scientist by any means but I like the scale of realism this fungus has and the design of it is amazing. Throughout the movie it scales up and more up and again I feel like it's super realistic for Naomi's character to naturally feel curious but ultimately doesn't go to far with it and for Travis to follow. Another thing to add the cinematography is absolutely amazing there was this one scene where \"One Way or Another\" by Blondie was playing in the background and during this they showed how this virus spread with a cockroach and how to reached Naomi's boyfriend. This was just a super cool watch. Throughout the movie there was plenty of funny moments and this kept you laughing but also at the edge of your seat.\n\nFinal verdict: \"Cold storage\" is a Horror, Si-Fi, comedy about two storage workers who must contain a deadly fungus. This film knows exactly what it wants to be and delivers a fast paced and funny movie that I will be recommending to friends.\n\nThe movie wasn't \"perfect\" or \"revolutionary\" to film or anything but it does what a movie is supposed to do. Entertain.\n\n8.5/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "26863d30-e6e1-423a-9e5f-309423d8439f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "044562fd42efc2be0650cfde4012476f9be6c5eea5d1e31fce88867ebeb23a00"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "STEFANO-619", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-09", "title": null, "content": "I found COLD STORAGE to be a truly entertaining sci-fi horror that leans into its B-movie roots with a witty and engaging script. While the \"mutating fungus\" plot might seem predictable at first, the chemistry between Joe Keery and Georgina Campbell is riveting and makes the characters feel like more than just targets. I had some reservations about the lackluster CGI in a few scenes, but the practical body horror effects were visceral and compelling. Overall, it's a solid piece of escapism that makes for a riveting watch."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "0ad7f237-9845-4338-9a3c-3a579e4f15ee", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "4fe14b50308cbd21f1bc8b923191555153417c7e0edfa1ab927b8ae2df7282aa"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "tucs26115", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage is good but not funny at all. I did not even know it was comedy till l looked it up after I watched it. This movie is a bit different and it's a nice watch Liam Neeson always delivers and Joe Keery was really good too. It could of gone either way with this movie but it did not disappoint and if you are into these kind of movies then you definitely will enjoy this one. I like the fungus virus type movies anyways an interesting watch. Overall a 6.3 for me too. It was a gooden just not funny. Still worth your time though\n\n2026 is gonna be a brill year for movies."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "17ee761d-d981-4b71-8206-2ba8dbd1d357", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "6897a063af611803cf7ecfefcae1162e0d083e1ec640dee83a08ca2333f3a328"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "DMM_Horror", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-08", "title": null, "content": "A really tense movie that kept me on edge. The idea that something like this fungus could actually exist and be locked away somewhere made it feel way more realistic and unsettling. The effects were solid and there were plenty of nail-biting moments as things kept getting worse. That's what stuck with me the most. Not the scariest movie ever, but definitely tense and a fun watch."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "2edd77e4-bb84-4c4f-ae2c-556b8496aafd", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a148f0cc17f82fa87e1ecfcef9985a22fa597ca248eab87cb7437d89779d6bce"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "RogerWilliamsUser", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-07", "title": null, "content": "This is a weird movie; but I think I know why.\n\nI enjoyed the story, well acted.\n\nBut still felt like a short story that was adapted. Some of the plot kinda felt like a couple of movies stitched together, quickly.\n\nSome of the acting felt rushed and definitely not polished. The CGI was good, but it felt just like another show.\n\nIt feels like the same methods, CGI, lighting and story telling as appeared in Five Nights At Freddy's 2. Chillingly similar.\n\nNot a bad way to spend time, but don't expect too much more than the usual."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "a6721e16-2464-46a0-8268-80b6c6b449b8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "4f5f959e271dc458e978cd23973683c508ab84a99790cdc883c06137c38919f7"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "lord-blade", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-03-11", "title": null, "content": "Cold Storage was an enjoyable movie.\n\nPretty simple premise, but played wonderfully. It was a comedy, but well done. Not just endless slapstick or stupid jokes like a lot of these end up being. There were good gags, some fun lines and overall just a fun time.\n\nThe special effects were very well done for a smaller budget movie.\n\nThe acting was great. The main characters came off as charming and lovable. Not the typical annoying \"why won't they shut up\" types you usually see in these films.\n\nThe pacing was really well done too. Normally these types of films end up being a lot of slow slog, followed by brief action, then waiting for the next thing to happen. This felt good. Slowly introducing things, setting up the plot, introducing characters and then things progressed at a steady pace, leading to the big action ending. I never once felt bored watching this, which is nice. And it didn't run too long either.\n\nThis movie was based on a novel that I'd never heard about, but I might have to check it out after watching the movie."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "35ec1579-84aa-4a8f-ac7f-e84b15eb3211", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e09629462ccd0e42e431cb0098f021d4d17131be86028b1173880f1b08dd2cd3"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "2Yung4This", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-03-10", "title": null, "content": "Could've been good but it's really bad none of the things make sense from start to end there is no reason for movies to be this dumb for things to happen. There are many great horror movies and games which these people can learn from just because it's a comedy doesn't mean it has to be braindead movie.\n\nThis feels like they took inspiration from resident evil and last of us but didn't bother writing a good plot and the zombies whole motivation is to spread by implosion? And because of that reason these zombies doesn't feel scary at all it make sense but there needs to be different types of zombies some should implode some should spread the fungus or virus other ways and i don't really understand what's the end goal of this fungus if it requires a host to spread but it does at the end there will no host so what than? In nature this exist but it's not as this fast spreading which make more sense as they need the host to survive not to eradicate the whole population.\n\nThe only reason I watched it because of steve from Stanger things and it was a hard watch and I like the guy none of the acting was good."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "fa1f6a66-565b-4f6d-9673-9c5f54d41ad1", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "8f33171da766389db2cea4e8e3e8b8b521054f26dc59c215fc896bb887c69b5d"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "niallmacmillan", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-22", "title": null, "content": "Fun enough but incredibly short....the end came just as it started to get going.\n\nI was expecting more of a comedy.... It doesn't take itself too seriously and there was a few funny moments but not an all out comedy like a Zombieland and definitely not that scary to be classed as a horror.\n\nGood stop gap movie to watch when it's out on streaming!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "a2e167ff-ce5b-4533-9124-0da3798effb5", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "b0e6cdbe07359a6d474dff3689eb80c3ed709e9cb2f8045a13b4369daf74a3ce"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "scorpiota-858585", "rating": 4, "date": "2026-03-09", "title": null, "content": "I wanted a comedy/horror movie to watch and thought this would be it. I was wrong. It tries to be funny, but it never plays out that way. And it is just one of those gross horror movies. Where instead of scary things happening, it's just nasty puss filled things exploding.\n\nIf you want a movie that just shows a bunch of decaying, puss filled stuff exploding, then this is your movie. Otherwise, definitely skip this!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "1c9385ac-fa57-4e70-8dce-bcf350de9e59", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "22900ef3967829bd5dff6c8cbc61e500f3df9a1f2680904e572a06f1b52d675e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "hooper-65382", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-03-10", "title": null, "content": "Not at all a zombie movie fan so all the more pleasantly surprised by this super fun comedy/horror film. Great to see Liam Neeson perfectly cast as a fungus hunter!\n\nGreat young (mostly) cast and fine special effects. Fun alien fungus kept rolling, splattering along pick up villain victims. All heroes imperiled but never doomed.\n\nAll in all a fun fest we can all enjoy!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "ab454d2a-09a8-4767-8e53-0013c0d179a2", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:18.802263", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "653f0fef64960292f1562a3bc09a170791140b1e53f5719b34351b7215e6d903"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt8879928", "author": "HelenA-6426", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-03-01", "title": null, "content": "The intro scene felt like Evolution meets Vietnam war films just a great hook in.\n\nEnd credits playing a kick ass DFTR a nod to Stephen King's The Stand I'm sure. Everything in between excellent pacing, great writing and acting and the effects were cool. I'll watch it again a few times no doubt.\n\nBased on a novel is usually a good sign and this don't disappoint."}}
